The '''Boulder River''' is a {{convert|77|mi|km|adj=on}} tributary of the [[Jefferson River]] in southwestern [[Montana]] in the United States.<ref name="assessment data"/> 

It rises in the [[Rocky Mountains]] at the [[continental divide]] in the [[Deerlodge National Forest]] in western [[Jefferson County, Montana|Jefferson County]]. It flows east and southeast through the mountains past [[Boulder, Montana|Boulder]], then south to join the Jefferson near [[Cardwell, Montana|Cardwell]].<ref name="topoquest Boulder River">{{cite web | author = United States Geological Survey (USGS) |title = United States Geological Survey Topographic Map | publisher = TopoQuest | url = http://www.topoquest.com/map.php?lat=45.866944&lon=-111.945556&datum=nad83&zoom=4| accessdate = January 23, 2013}}</ref>

[[Game fish]] in the river include [[Brook trout|brook]], [[Brown trout|brown]], and [[Rainbow trout|rainbow]] trout, and [[mountain whitefish]].<ref name="waterbody report">{{cite web|title=Detailed Waterbody Report: Boulder River
|url=http://fwp.mt.gov/fishing/guide/waterbodyDetail.html?llid=1119459458671|publisher=Montana Fish, Wildlife & Parks|accessdate=January 23, 2013}}</ref> Brown trout are most prevalent in the last {{convert|2|mi|km|0}}, near the mouth, and the other three species are more prevalent in the reach upstream of the town of Boulder.<ref name="waterbody report"/> The lowermost {{convert|12|mi|km}} of the river is affected by irrigation withdrawals, and the reach below the community of [[Basin, Montana|Basin]] is affected by seepage from old mines and tailings.<ref name="waterbody report"/>

